29
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Seeking to bury any notion that corporate law bound its actors to comply with non-corporate law, Professors Easterbrook and Fischel declared, \u8220\'3f[m]anagers have no general obligation to avoid violating regulatory laws, when violations are profitable to the firm.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F30357692861_ID0E6VAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F30357692861_ID0E6VAE_1}
