{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EWWAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EWWAE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Meanwhile, corporate law reforms were busy at work to ensure that corporate law did not obligate corporate actors to comply with non-corporate legal norms. Courts (and commentators) announced a \u8220\'3fnet-loss rule\u8221\'3f that assumed directors who permitted illegal activity could not be liable to the corporation unless the loss arising from the violation exceeded any gains the corporation garnered from the illegality--namely, a net loss.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F32357692861_ID0EBXAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F32357692861_ID0EBXAE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F32357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
32
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The assumption was that only \u8220\'3fegregious law violations involving large damages\u8221\'3f could be actionable-- though such cases never arose.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F33357692861_ID0EOXAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F33357692861_ID0EOXAE_1}
