}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, though re-categorizing the duty from one of care to loyalty, confirmed the fiduciary duty of corporate actors to ensure compliance.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F44357692861_ID0EN4AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F44357692861_ID0EN4AE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F44357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
44
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EU4AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EU4AE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Admittedly, no case has imposed personal liability on directors for violating their duty to ensure legal compliance. But that duty, now buttressed by the certification and disclosure requirements of Sarbanes-Oxley,
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F45357692861_ID0E44AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F45357692861_ID0E44AE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F45357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
45
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 is not without normative content. The threat of personal liability has spawned a whole industry in internal controls and a corporate aversion to being seen as consciously disregarding legal norms.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F46357692861_ID0EE5AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F46357692861_ID0EE5AE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F46357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
46
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EL5AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EL5AE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In summary, the duty of obedience lives. But lacking a proper vocabulary, courts and commentators have gone in search for a category into which to fit it.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F47357692861_ID0EW5AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F47357692861_ID0EW5AE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F47357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
47
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 While 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Caremark
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 said compliance was a matter of care and 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Stone v. Ritter
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 said it involved good faith, a subset of loyalty, the truth is that diligence and personal fidelity in pursuit of legal compliance are simply aspects of obedience to law.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EP6AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EP6AE_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
II. DUTY OF OBEDIENCE IN THE NON-PROFIT CORPORATION
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EZ6AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EZ6AE_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The duty of obedience has a clearer and more-established pedigree in the nonprofit corporation. It is regularly mentioned along with the duties of care and loyalty. The legal literature devotes a good deal of attention to its contours and its place in non- 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1500_467_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1500_467_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*467
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 profit law. Court cases apply the duty to require non-profit actors to ensure compliance with the non-profit\rquote s mission, donative restrictions, and tax requirements.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F48357692861_ID0EPAAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F48357692861_ID0EPAAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F48357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
48
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EWAAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EWAAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
This is not surprising. The non-profit corporation exists to serve social purposes, as embodied in both internal and external norms.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F49357692861_ID0EBBAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F49357692861_ID0EBBAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F49357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
49
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Compliance with these norms is not only central to the legitimacy of the non-profit corporation, but frames the duties imposed on its actors. The non-profit vocabulary of \u8220\'3fmission\u8221\'3f and \u8220\'3ftrustee\u8221\'3f suggests the degree of obedience that non-profit fiduciaries owe to the organization.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F50357692861_ID0EIBAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F50357692861_ID0EIBAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F50357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
50
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EPBAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EPBAG_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
A. Scope of Non-Profit Duty of Obedience
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EZBAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EZBAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The leading textbook on non-profit law explains that non-profit trustees have a duty \u8220\'3fto carry out the purposes of the organization as expressed in the articles or certificate of incorporation.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F51357692861_ID0EKCAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F51357692861_ID0EKCAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F51357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
51
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The duty has been summarized as:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
mandat[ing] that the board refrain from transactions and activities that are ultra vires, that is, beyond the corporation\rquote s powers and purposes as expressed in its certificate of incorporation .... Thus, the director must follow the purposes and powers expressed in the governing legal documents.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F52357692861_ID0E4CAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F52357692861_ID0E4CAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F52357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
52
}}}
\sb200 
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EHDAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EHDAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The obedience duty therefore tracks and reinforces the non-profit\rquote s mission-- \u8220\'3fto act with fidelity, within the bounds of the law generally, to the organization\rquote s \u8216\'3fmission.\u8221\'3f\u8217\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F53357692861_ID0EZDAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F53357692861_ID0EZDAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F53357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
53
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EBEAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EBEAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Commentators have also pointed out that, beyond complying with internal norms, non-profit fiduciaries also must ensure the non-profit complies with external legal regimes \u8220\'3franging from federal and state tax laws, civil rights statutes, and antitrust laws which affect all organizations.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F54357692861_ID0ESEAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F54357692861_ID0ESEAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F54357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
54
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The consequences of non-compliance by non-profit directors may be even more onerous than for their for-profit brethren:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1500_468_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1500_468_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*468
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
 A [non-profit fiduciary] can be held responsible if an organization violates the law. For example, a director or officer is liable for a corporation\rquote s failure to pay taxes if she meets the Internal Revenue Code\rquote s definition of \u8220\'3f[responsible] person\u8221\'3f and the failure to pay has been \u8220\'3fwillful.\u8221\'3f Directors involved in day-to-day administration of the organization in matters related to taxes and financial records are \u8220\'3f[responsible] persons.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F55357692861_ID0EMFAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F55357692861_ID0EMFAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F55357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
55
}}}
\sb200 
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EWFAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EWFAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Some commentators even argue that the duty of obedience \u8220\'3fis more basic, [constituting instead] the foundation on which the duties of care and loyalty ultimately rest.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F56357692861_ID0EHGAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F56357692861_ID0EHGAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F56357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
56
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Some courts echo the view, pointing out that non-profit directors must be \u8220\'3fprincipally concerned about the effective performance of the nonprofit\rquote s mission.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F57357692861_ID0EUGAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F57357692861_ID0EUGAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F57357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
57
}}}
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E2GAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E2GAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Besides garnering attention from commentators, the duty of obedience has been a mainstay of non-profit case law, both as a stand-alone duty and as a subset of the duty of loyalty. A leading case, involving the proposed sale of a non-profit hospital, turned on whether the sale furthered the \u8220\'3fpurposes of the corporation.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F58357692861_ID0EGHAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F58357692861_ID0EGHAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F58357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
58
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In describing the duty to further corporate purposes, the court explained:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
It is axiomatic that the Board of Directors is charged with the duty to ensure that the mission of the charitable corporation is carried out. This duty has been referred to as the \u8220\'3fduty of obedience.\u8221\'3f It requires the director of a not-for-profit corporation to \u8220\'3fbe faithful to the purposes and goals of the organization,\u8221\'3f since \u8220\'3f[u]nlike business corporations, whose ultimate objective is to make money, nonprofit corporations are defined by their specific objectives: perpetuation of particular activities are central to the 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
raison d\rquote etre
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
 of the organization.\u8221\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F59357692861_ID0EQIAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F59357692861_ID0EQIAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F59357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
59
}}}
\sb200 
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E1IAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E1IAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The duty of obedience also requires compliance with the tax laws, which define the scope and purposes of qualifying non-profits. As the leading non-profits casebook explains:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The duty of obedience often arises in the tax context. Organizations exempt from taxation under \u167\'3f 501(c)(3) ... must be organized and operated exclusively for certain approved purposes .... If an organization is operated for nonexempt purposes, the directors have violated their duty of obedience .... 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_1500_469_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_1500_469_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*469
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
 Directors should have in place procedures and systems that are likely to assure compliance and enable them to monitor compliance appropriately.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F60357692861_ID0EBKAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F60357692861_ID0EBKAG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F60357692861_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
60
}}}
\sb200 
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0ELKAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0ELKAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In short, while an explicit duty of obedience in the for-profit corporation disappeared with the demise of the ultra vires doctrine--at least, in its old-time-religion form--the duty of obedience in the non-profit corporation continues to have vitality. It guides non-profit fiduciaries in carrying out the mission of the organization, consistent with the many legal regimes that non-profits inhabit.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E1KAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E1KAG_1}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
B. Survival of Obedience Duty in an Age of Non-Profit Adaptability
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EELAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EELAG_1}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The privatization movement has also seeped into the non-profit corporate world. Just as the for-profit corporation is seen as a private adaptation to the business, financial, and legal landscapes in which it operates, the non-profit corporation has come under pressure to get with the times. Old missions must be updated, dead hands must be buried, and non-profit fiduciaries must focus on the bottom line. As a recent treatise author has explained:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri400 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li700 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb400 
To the extent the duty of obedience does not carry with it a duty to assure that the trust is meeting contemporaneous needs, it does not set forth an appropriate standard.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F61357692861_ID0EAMAG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F61357692861_ID0EAMAG_1}
